content:
Upgrade your Sales Analytics app when a new version is released. A banner at the top of your home page tells you that a new version is available, and a link invites you to start the upgrade process.

Click "What's new" or "New version available" to read information about the new version. At the bottom of the page, find the buttons: Upgrade current app and Create new app.

- Clicking Upgrade current app overwrites your current app and all its assets, deleting any customizations.
- Clicking Create new app creates a second copy of your current app based on the new version, preserving the current version and any customizations.

If you've customized your app, click Create new app to preserve your changes. If you're OK with overwriting your current app, check the box and click Continue to proceed with upgrading.

After clicking either button, go through the configuration wizard to set up your upgraded or new app. Review the screen that indicates which assets are impacted by the upgrade.

If you're creating a new app, name it something different from the current version and click Create new app.
title: Upgrading CRM Analytics Apps
